##
## Select it with CONDSTORE enabled

C: 1e SELECT alpha (CONDSTORE)
S: \* FLAGS \(\\Answered \\Deleted \\Draft \\Flagged \\Seen\)
S: \* 4 EXISTS
S: \* 4 RECENT
S: \* OK \[UIDVALIDITY \d+\].*
S: \* OK \[UNSEEN 1\].*
S: \* OK \[PERMANENTFLAGS \(\\Answered \\Deleted \\Draft \\Flagged \\\Seen( \\\*)?\)\].*
S: \* OK \[HIGHESTMODSEQ \d+\].*
S: \* OK \[UIDNEXT 5\].*
S: 1e OK \[READ-WRITE\] SELECT completed.

## Check stored messages before getting started
C: 1f FETCH 1:* (FLAGS)
S: \* 1 FETCH \(FLAGS \(\\Recent\)\)
S: \* 2 FETCH \(FLAGS \(\\Recent\)\)
S: \* 3 FETCH \(FLAGS \(\\Recent\)\)
S: \* 4 FETCH \(FLAGS \(\\Recent\)\)
S: 1f OK FETCH completed.

## All messages has modseq 5 because of the \RECENT reset while selecting

C: 1g STORE 1:* (UNCHANGEDSINCE 1) FLAGS (\Deleted)
S: 1g OK \[MODIFIED 0 1:4\] STORE failed.

C: 1h STORE 1:2 (UNCHANGEDSINCE 5) +FLAGS (\DRAFT)
S: \* 1 FETCH \(MODSEQ \(\d+\) FLAGS \(\\Draft \\Recent\)\)
S: \* 2 FETCH \(MODSEQ \(\d+\) FLAGS \(\\Draft \\Recent\)\)
S: 1h OK Conditional STORE completed.

## Message 2 have a modseq > 5 thus update will fail on them
## Message 3 and 4 will be updated

C: 1i STORE 2:4 (UNCHANGEDSINCE 5) +FLAGS (\ANSWERED)
S: \* 3 FETCH \(MODSEQ \(\d+\) FLAGS \(\\Answered \\Recent\)\)
S: \* 4 FETCH \(MODSEQ \(\d+\) FLAGS \(\\Answered \\Recent\)\)
S: 1i OK \[MODIFIED 0 2\] STORE failed.
## TODO buggy. Do not conform with example in RFC-4551 sections 3.2
## TODO MODIFIED should not include 0

## Check messages 1 2 3 and 4

C: 1j FETCH 1:* (FLAGS)
S: \* 1 FETCH \(FLAGS \(\\Draft \\Recent\)\)
S: \* 2 FETCH \(FLAGS \(\\Draft \\Recent\)\)
S: \* 3 FETCH \(FLAGS \(\\Answered \\Recent\)\)
S: \* 4 FETCH \(FLAGS \(\\Answered \\Recent\)\)
S: 1j OK FETCH completed.

## Check since update 1h -> modseq 6
C: 1k FETCH 1:* (FLAGS) (CHANGEDSINCE 6)
S: \* 3 FETCH \(MODSEQ \(\d+\) FLAGS \(\\Answered \\Recent\)\)
S: \* 4 FETCH \(MODSEQ \(\d+\) FLAGS \(\\Answered \\Recent\)\)
S: 1k OK FETCH completed.